{"title": "Testing positive for Covid in 'zero-Covid' China", "tags": "asia", "timestamp": "2022-06-11", "content": "Living in China and reporting on the country's pandemic travails for the last two and a half years, I thought I was already very familiar with its severe Covid policies.\nThen in May, on my way back after my first visit to Singapore in two years, I tested positive for Covid-19 at Shanghai Pudong International Airport."}